# /agent-all pipeline (Cursor port)

This workspace has the `/agent-all` Cursor kit installed. When the user
invokes `@agent-all-coordinator`, follow the 7 phases documented in
`plugins/harness-floor-cursor/skills/agent-all-cursor/phases/`:

| Phase | File | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| 0 | `0-preflight.md` | git + .cursor/agents/ + config + input checks |
| 1 | `1-intent.md` | brainstorming OR load task file |
| 2 | `2-plan.md` | draft plan into `.agent-skill/plans/` |
| 3 | `3-dispatch.md` | fan out to `@agent-all-implementer` (parallel) |
| 4 | `4-gate.md` | fan out to `@agent-all-reviewer` |
| 5 | `5-pr.md` | branch push + `gh pr create` |
| 6 | `6-loop.md` | breakCondition shell loop |

## Cursor-specific rules

1. **Use `is_background: true` subagents for parallelism.** `agent-all-implementer`
   and `agent-all-reviewer` both have it. Cursor's planner runs them concurrently.
2. **State file `.agent-all-state.json`** — coordinator writes via Cursor's
   edit surface. Schema matches the Claude Code orchestrator.
3. **Loop continue is manual.** Cursor cannot auto-re-invoke a chat; the
   coordinator emits an "Iter N+1 ready, send continue" message and waits.
4. **Cost tracking is best-effort.** Cursor's chat surface doesn't expose
   per-turn cost — the coordinator records only what the user pastes back.

## Config

`.agent-all.json` at workspace root. Schema same as Claude Code. Defaults
ship in `templates/agent-all.config.json.hbs`.

## Source-of-truth

`plugins/harness-floor/skills/agent-all/SKILL.md` is the canonical pipeline
design. Cursor's port adapts the dispatch primitives but preserves the
phase contract.
